<section id="sec.intro">
<title>Introduction</title> 

<para>This guide provides instructions for installing &sr;, its third
party libraries, the (optional) <acronym>PETSc</acronym> and Insight
libraries, sample data sets, and &sr; documentation.</para>

<para> The <ulink
url="http://www-unix.mcs.anl.gov/petsc/petsc-2/"><acronym>PETSc</acronym></ulink>
library adds equation solvers to &sr;'s SolveMatrix module.  The
<ulink url="http://www.itk.org">Insight Toolkit
(<acronym>ITK</acronym>)</ulink> provides segmentation, registration,
and image processing filters encapsulated as &sr; modules.
</para>

<para>
&sr; has been tested on three platforms: SGI, Linux, and Mac OS X.
Platform requirement guidelines are listed in <xref
linkend="tbl.pltfm_req"/>.
</para>

<para>
Disk space requirements for build from source code are listed in <xref
linkend="tbl.disk_space"/>.
</para>

<para>See <xref linkend="intro.nvidia_notes"
endterm="intro.nvidia_notes.title"/> for information on the use of
Nvidia graphics cards with the Linux operating system.</para>

<para>See <xref endterm="intro.ati_notes.title"
linkend="intro.ati_notes"/> for information on the use of ATI cards
and drivers with the Linux operating system.</para>

<para>See <xref linkend="intro.redhat_ent_notes"
endterm="intro.redhat_ent_notes.title"/> for information about the use
of Red Hat Enterprise Linux.</para>

